{
    "info": {
        "name": "Doctorna API v2 (Minimal & Clean)",
        "description": "# Doctorna API v2\n\nThis collection has been strictly optimized. All redundant endpoints have been removed. \n\n## \ud83d\udd0d How Filtering Works\nOur API is smart. You do **not** need to hit separate \"filter\" endpoints or send custom headers.\n\nTo filter data, simply add query parameters to any `GET` request!\n\n**Examples:**\n- `GET /doctors` -> Returns all doctors.\n- `GET /doctors?gender=female&rank=specialist` -> Automatically returns filtered doctors.\n- `GET /specialities?name=Dentist` -> Returns specific specialities.\n- `GET /appointments?status=pending` -> Returns pending appointments.\n\n## \ud83d\udcca Bonus Features (Query Flags)\n- `GET /specialities?id=1&include_doctors=1` -> Appends a `doctors_count` field to the speciality response.",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "1. Authentication",
            "description": "Endpoints for user registration, login, and password recovery.",
            "item": [
